1
00:00:04,719 --> 00:00:06,577
Knowledge above mortality.

2
00:00:07,407 --> 00:00:15,613
It has to be knowledge that’s
beyond limited world usefulness.

3
00:00:15,663 --> 00:00:18,053
[Mind | Frenemy]

4
00:00:18,173 --> 00:00:24,211
āmnāyaḥ prāha tattvaṁ harim iha
paramaṁ sarva-śaktim rasābdhim
[Daśa-mūla-tattva]

5
00:00:24,211 --> 00:00:26,471
Means ‘descending’—
what’s descending 
 

6
00:00:26,471 --> 00:00:29,794
into this plane
through divine agency.

7
00:00:30,274 --> 00:00:35,510
In other words, do you think it would be 
a good idea if you could talk to Kṛṣṇa

8
00:00:35,510 --> 00:00:38,296
right now and say, 
“Kṛṣṇa, what should I do?”

9
00:00:38,298 --> 00:00:41,191
Do you think that 
would be valuable?

10
00:00:42,113 --> 00:00:45,948
And you think He would give, 
like, a proper …

11
00:00:45,948 --> 00:00:48,749
That you would say, “No, but You 
don’t understand my situation.”

12
00:00:48,749 --> 00:00:52,968
He’d go, “No, I do, I expand through 
Paramātmā, I am fully aware of …”

13
00:00:52,968 --> 00:00:57,096
—No, no, no. Let me explain some things 
to You, like, have happened recently.

14
00:00:57,096 --> 00:00:58,696
—No, I’m also aware
of those things.

15
00:00:58,696 --> 00:01:01,568
—No, but I mean, do You really know
how I feel about all this?

16
00:01:01,568 --> 00:01:04,749
—I think I know 
how you feel about it too.

17
00:01:05,509 --> 00:01:08,758
So, the Absolute Personality 
of Godhead have an idea

18
00:01:08,758 --> 00:01:12,575
about what your situation is
and what happened.

19
00:01:12,575 --> 00:01:13,975
“The guy this afternoon …

20
00:01:13,975 --> 00:01:16,895
You don’t understand, 
like, what happened.”

21
00:01:16,895 --> 00:01:20,320
No, I mean He should know 
what happened.

22
00:01:20,320 --> 00:01:23,176
And so, and He can say, 
“Well, I produced … 
 

23
00:01:23,176 --> 00:01:27,636
see, ’cause I can see
a lot of stuff,

24
00:01:27,636 --> 00:01:31,745
I made these books that have 
this type of advice in it,

25
00:01:31,745 --> 00:01:33,977
and then I’ve got people 
who can interpret them,

26
00:01:33,977 --> 00:01:36,828
and if you connect with them,
they can give you some good guidance.”

27
00:01:36,828 --> 00:01:38,665
—“Are you sure?”

28
00:01:38,665 --> 00:01:45,071
“I’m pretty sure about it. 
I thought it out, way in advance.

29
00:01:45,071 --> 00:01:49,520
I’ve been doing this creation after 
creation—it gets old after a while.”

30
00:01:49,520 --> 00:01:51,103
[Laughing]

31
00:01:51,103 --> 00:01:53,905
I mean, 
what are we thinking?

32
00:01:54,584 --> 00:01:58,668
We’re thinking God is some 
character on a sitcom.

33
00:01:59,678 --> 00:02:04,939
Where you can just, “Aha-ha-ha”—
just laugh it off.

34
00:02:06,449 --> 00:02:11,949
The Absolute Entity, 
the Supreme Reality …

35
00:02:14,289 --> 00:02:17,009
And … as the writer says,
[D. F. Wallace]

36
00:02:17,009 --> 00:02:23,499
“We cherish being the lords
of our skull-sized kingdoms.”

37
00:02:23,499 --> 00:02:30,789
And we’re suspicious of allowing
any sort of divine revelation

38
00:02:30,920 --> 00:02:35,430
or suggestion enter that domain.

39
00:02:37,560 --> 00:02:40,540
So we’re the cause 
of our own misfortune.

40
00:02:40,540 --> 00:02:44,277
uddhared ātmanātmānam 
nātmānam avasādayet

41
00:02:44,277 --> 00:02:49,497
ātmaiva hy ātmano bandhur, 
ātmaiva ripur ātmanaḥ 
[Bg: 6.5]

42
00:02:49,497 --> 00:02:53,223
So Kṛṣṇa tells Arjuna, 
“Your mind, ātmā”—
 

43
00:02:53,223 --> 00:02:56,223
your sense of self,
you can say,

44
00:02:56,223 --> 00:02:59,978
because I mean it says ‘ātmā’, 
ātmanātmānam—well ... the ‘mind’.

45
00:03:00,038 --> 00:03:05,051
Taking the mind 
as the best adviser of yourself—

46
00:03:05,051 --> 00:03:09,811
not a good idea according 
to Kṛṣṇa and Bhagavad-gītā.

47
00:03:10,776 --> 00:03:14,056
He’s saying, 
"But it can become

48
00:03:14,056 --> 00:03:17,897
friendly to you,
and your needs, necessities,

49
00:03:17,897 --> 00:03:20,897
your mission, your purpose, 
your direction—

50
00:03:20,897 --> 00:03:26,697
if it can become infused 
with spiritual consideration,

51
00:03:26,697 --> 00:03:29,498
if it becomes known to us 
through the agency:

52
00:03:29,498 --> 00:03:34,160
sādhu, śāstra, 
guru and Vaiṣṇav.”

53
00:03:34,160 --> 00:03:38,064
That’s why day one, what does 
Guru Maharāj say to Gurudev?

54
00:03:38,064 --> 00:03:41,794
“Are you prepared to listen to me 
and not your mind?”

55
00:03:41,812 --> 00:03:43,558
It’s the first thing 
he says to him

56
00:03:43,558 --> 00:03:46,908
because he knows, if that’s not 
at the basis of the relationship,

57
00:03:46,908 --> 00:03:49,328
it’s going to be meaningless.

58
00:03:49,328 --> 00:03:52,908
He’s not going to make progress. 
He is not going to go very far.

59
00:03:52,908 --> 00:03:58,058
It’s going to be a show of servitude,
submission, discipleship.

60
00:03:58,058 --> 00:04:03,783
“But if you’re going to follow me
and resist the suggestions of your mind,

61
00:04:03,783 --> 00:04:06,193
then you’re going 
to make progress.”

62
00:04:06,193 --> 00:04:08,453
asat-saṅga-tyāga,—ei vaiṣṇava-ācāra
[Cc: 2.22.87]

63
00:04:08,453 --> 00:04:16,415
So that asat-saṅga to tyāga is the mind 
and the suggestions of the mind.

64
00:04:16,415 --> 00:04:20,220
What Prabhupād once referred 
to as ‘eating the mind’s bananas’.

65
00:04:20,240 --> 00:04:21,710
[Laughing]

